A 29-year-old man, Tosin Adepoju, was yesterday arraigned before an Ikeja Magistratesâ€™ Court for allegedly defrauding two women of N800,000 Adepoju and others now at large were charged on a five-count charge of conspiracy, stealing and false pretence before Magistrate O Sule-Amuzat. Prosecuting Inspector Benson Emeurhi told the court that the defendant committed the alleged offence on March 28 in Ikeja. According to Emeurhi, the defendant was alleged to have obtained the sum of N300,000 from one Tolani Jones with a pretence to help her procure clothing materials. Emeurhi further informed the court that the defendant also fraudulently obtained N500, 000 from Oluwaseun Ariyo with a pretence to help her procure clothing materials. The defendant pleaded not guilty. Magistrate Sule-Amzat granted him N50,000 bail with two sureties in the like sum. She ordered that the address of the sureties be verified and adjourned the case till June 7. 